00:30:24,038 --> 00:30:26,268
but that might just be
about the deal in general.

476
00:30:26,341 --> 00:30:28,935
I mean, "perfect counterfeit currency. "

477
00:30:29,010 --> 00:30:31,376
That's an oxymoron
if ever I heard one, right?

478
00:30:31,446 --> 00:30:33,812
What is this sideshow, huh?

479
00:30:33,882 --> 00:30:36,942
He's telling the truth, though,
when he says that the counterfeit's perfect.

480
00:30:37,018 --> 00:30:41,785
He truly- He does believe that.
But then again, he's just, uh-

481
00:30:41,856 --> 00:30:45,451
He's what's-his-name, uh,
down at the U.N. all over again, right?

482
00:30:45,527 --> 00:30:47,688
Uh, excuse me?

483
00:30:47,762 --> 00:30:53,394
That guy, he truly did believe
all that W. M.D. nonsense.

484
00:30:53,468 --> 00:30:58,701
So, cleverly, they sent him off
down to the U.N. to sell it.

485
00:30:58,773 --> 00:31:00,468
Rest is history.

486
00:31:00,542 --> 00:31:02,339
No one sent me here.

487
00:31:04,812 --> 00:31:09,044
The currency... is flawless.

488
00:31:10,251 --> 00:31:12,276
Nah. Uh-

489
00:31:12,353 --> 00:31:16,255
I mean, I'm sorry,
but it's not good enough.

490
00:31:16,324 --> 00:31:18,588
Who is this ass, huh?

491
00:31:18,660 --> 00:31:21,220
Screw him. Let's go.

492
00:31:21,296 --> 00:31:23,992
We're not done yet.

493
00:31:27,201 --> 00:31:30,364
- No! You swore to me that you wouldn't-
- Hey, hey!

494
00:31:30,438 --> 00:31:33,202
Is he telling the truth,
Dr. Lightman? Yes or no?

495
00:31:33,274 --> 00:31:36,175
Yes! Well, he believes that he is, yes.

496
00:31:36,244 --> 00:31:39,577
Good. So do we have a deal or not, huh?

497
00:31:42,483 --> 00:31:45,213
Is this the best you got,
Professor Lightman?

498
00:31:45,286 --> 00:31:47,220
Because so far, I'm underwhelmed.

499
00:31:47,288 --> 00:31:48,949
Or is there more?

500
00:31:49,023 --> 00:31:51,856
Right. Well, you put me in front
of the actual counterfeiter...

501
00:31:51,926 --> 00:31:55,089
with the bank notes in his hands...

502
00:31:55,163 --> 00:31:57,563
and I'll know
just how good his product is.

503
00:32:05,273 --> 00:32:09,710
Just you. Terry can stay here.

504
00:32:09,777 --> 00:32:11,904
No. Terry's with me.

505
00:32:13,014 --> 00:32:14,675
It's not negotiable.

506
00:32:14,749 --> 00:32:17,047
- No. I'll be all right.
- Don't be daft.

507
00:32:17,118 --> 00:32:20,019
- You need to be thinking about yourself right now.
- Yeah, now you tell me.

508
00:32:20,088 --> 00:32:21,749
It's not negotiable.

509
00:32:30,298 --> 00:32:32,095
Come on!

510
00:32:35,336 --> 00:32:37,998
Say nothin', Terry. Not a word.

511
00:32:41,009 --> 00:32:44,240
This is him?
It's your counterfeiter, right?

512
00:32:44,312 --> 00:32:48,442
The best there is.
Fifty thousand Euros, right there.

513
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:54,420
Bloody hell.

514
00:32:56,224 --> 00:32:59,489
- How many containers you got?
- That is not your concern.

515
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:01,994
Put it back.

516
00:33:03,331 --> 00:33:06,494
All right, um- What's your name?

517
00:33:06,567 --> 00:33:09,127
- He doesn't need to know that.
- I've got to establish a baseline here-

518
00:33:09,203 --> 00:33:10,966
easy answers to easy questions.

519
00:33:11,039 --> 00:33:14,270
- Then I can get to the bigger questions.
- Otto.

520
00:33:15,376 --> 00:33:19,073
- Hammil.
- Otto.

521
00:33:19,147 --> 00:33:20,808
What's your real last name?

522
00:33:22,083 --> 00:33:24,017
- Frankel.
- Yeah.

523
00:33:25,253 --> 00:33:26,948
- How many kids you got?
- None.

524
00:33:27,021 --> 00:33:28,682
- How long you been married?
- I'm not married.

525
00:33:28,756 --> 00:33:30,485
- Where you from?
- Chicago.

526
00:33:30,558 --> 00:33:33,026
Hey, get on with it, please, will you?

527
00:33:33,094 --> 00:33:36,962
All right. Um, these notes
are counterfeit, right?

528
00:33:37,031 --> 00:33:40,159
- Yes.
- How good are they?

529
00:33:40,234 --> 00:33:44,068
We already tested a modest amount
without detection.

530
00:33:44,138 --> 00:33:47,801
- Well, Dr. Lightman?
- What?

531
00:33:48,943 --> 00:33:51,207
Well, he hasn't answered my question yet.

532
00:33:53,414 --> 00:33:55,473
Easy, fellas. It's taken care of.

533
00:33:56,751 --> 00:33:59,845
He was right. F.B.I.

534
00:34:02,590 --> 00:34:06,549
- Okay.
- I don't think I can do this.

535
00:34:06,627 --> 00:34:09,528
I'll be right here
the whole time. Don't worry.

536
00:34:10,765 --> 00:34:12,699
Just take your time, Stacey.

537
00:34:19,240 --> 00:34:23,438
You knew what they were
doing to me, Mr. Fitzgerald.

538
00:34:23,511 --> 00:34:26,912
You didn't just ignore it...

539
00:34:26,981 --> 00:34:28,915
you started it all.

540
00:34:28,983 --> 00:34:32,077
- Oh, Stacey-
- You kept telling me...

541
00:34:32,153 --> 00:34:35,611
I was fat and lazy in front of them.

542
00:34:35,690 --> 00:34:38,284
- The-That's not true.
- Your hands and eyes say otherwise.

543
00:34:38,359 --> 00:34:40,554
So do I.

544
00:34:42,230 --> 00:34:44,221
I'm so sorry, Stacey.

545
00:34:44,298 --> 00:34:47,631
You know, I had a coach like you once...

546
00:34:47,702 --> 00:34:50,432
who had it in
for one of the kids on the team.

547
00:34:50,505 --> 00:34:54,965
Constant verbal abuse
disguised as authority.

548
00:34:55,042 --> 00:35:00,036
Eddie, Eddie Johnston. And nothin' that
Eddie ever did was ever good enough.

549
00:35:00,114 --> 00:35:03,811
- You're out of line.
- And the example that that coach set for the rest of us...

550
00:35:03,885 --> 00:35:06,718
just like you did for Jasmine
and all of her buddies...

551
00:35:06,788 --> 00:35:11,657
we thought it gave us the license
to make Eddie an outcast.

552
00:35:11,726 --> 00:35:14,388
I never touched a hair on her head.

553
00:35:14,462 --> 00:35:17,989
Right. Because we did it for you.

554
00:35:19,667 --> 00:35:23,626
I wanted you to have to live
the rest of your life-

555
00:35:23,704 --> 00:35:28,300
knowing that what you did to me made me-

556
00:35:34,549 --> 00:35:37,347
You knew what this
was really about all the time.

557
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:42,447
I know, because I sent you a video too.

558
00:35:42,523 --> 00:35:46,926
Which you, uh,
neglected to mention, Mr. Fitzgerald.

559
00:35:46,994 --> 00:35:48,825
Making you guilty
of obstruction of justice.

560
00:35:48,896 --> 00:35:52,593
And if this keeps you
away from kids forever, I'll take it.

561
00:35:52,667 --> 00:35:54,601
Right, Stacey?

562
00:35:55,670 --> 00:35:56,864
Yeah.

563
00:35:56,938 --> 00:36:00,635
Wait a minute. One kid has a-
has a psychological breakdown...

564
00:36:00,708 --> 00:36:03,677
an illness, and I'm to blame?

565
00:36:08,749 --> 00:36:10,683
- Come on. We need to-
- I don't-

566
00:36:14,455 --> 00:36:16,389
Thank you.

567
00:36:18,192 --> 00:36:20,660
Well, there's a whitening
of the skin around the eyes...

568
00:36:20,728 --> 00:36:24,687
which is a dead giveaway for the kind
of fear that we try to hide when we lie.

569
00:36:24,765 --> 00:36:28,223
And, uh, slight rotation of the right arm...

570
00:36:28,302 --> 00:36:31,203
which is what we call in the trade
a shrug fragment, which means...

571
00:36:31,272 --> 00:36:33,035
he's got zero confidence
in what he just said.

572
00:36:33,107 --> 00:36:37,567
The eyes of a cheat...

573
00:36:37,645 --> 00:36:39,306
who thinks he has all the cards...

574
00:36:39,380 --> 00:36:43,646
but who knows I'm telling the truth.

575
00:36:52,560 --> 00:36:54,221
Well, he's Lying.

576
00:36:54,295 --> 00:36:56,695
This son of a bitch has been
playin' us the whole time.

577
00:36:56,764 --> 00:36:58,425
Whoa. Easy. No, I didn't say-

578
00:36:58,499 --> 00:37:01,491
- You really think we're that dumb?
- Easy. No, I didn't say-

579
00:37:01,569 --> 00:37:03,264
No, no!

580
00:37:03,337 --> 00:37:05,669
F.B.I.! Nobody move!

581
00:37:07,775 --> 00:37:09,743
Anybody else?

582
00:37:09,810 --> 00:37:11,835
Down on your knees! Now!

583
00:37:11,913 --> 00:37:14,040
Move! Move! Down!

584
00:37:14,115 --> 00:37:16,083
On your knees! Do it!

585
00:37:32,800 --> 00:37:34,791
How'd you do that?

586
00:37:37,138 --> 00:37:39,299
- Blanks.
- Blanks?

587
00:37:39,373 --> 00:37:42,308
No, no, I mean with your eyes.
How do you do that?

588
00:37:42,376 --> 00:37:44,105
Oh, it was... just practice.

589
00:37:44,178 --> 00:37:46,544
What's going on?

590
00:37:46,614 --> 00:37:49,378
- Get up.
- Oh, blimey.

591
00:37:49,450 --> 00:37:51,077
Put your hands behind your back.

592
00:37:51,152 --> 00:37:53,985
I swear, I'm gettin'
too old for this, Terry. I really am.

593
00:37:54,055 --> 00:37:58,651
F.B.I. have been onto you
and McClellan for a while now.

594
00:37:58,726 --> 00:38:01,092
- Special Agent Hutton.
- Oh, nice to meet you.

595
00:38:01,162 --> 00:38:04,825
You too. Superior work, Agent Reynolds.

596
00:38:04,899 --> 00:38:07,561
Likewise, my friend.
So, how's that for having your back?

597
00:38:07,635 --> 00:38:09,933
Just like a real F.B.I. agent.

598
00:38:10,004 --> 00:38:12,165
- Thanks a lot, Cal.
- What?

599
00:38:12,239 --> 00:38:15,265
So, uh- When'd you first
realize I was undercover, Dr. Lightman?

600
00:38:15,343 --> 00:38:17,334
Back at the poker table.

601
00:38:17,411 --> 00:38:21,871
You were angry and fearful,
but on my behalf.

602
00:38:24,785 --> 00:38:26,446
- Really?
- Yeah.

603
00:38:26,520 --> 00:38:28,613
Come on. Let's go.

604
00:38:28,689 --> 00:38:31,920
Ben? Hold on a sec.

605
00:38:31,993 --> 00:38:34,985
I tell you what.
Terry walks for his part in this.

606
00:38:35,062 --> 00:38:38,520
- What?
- And then we're evens.

607
00:38:38,599 --> 00:38:41,193
You know I couldn't
have done this without him.

608
00:38:46,307 --> 00:38:49,242
He goes from here to the airport,
and he doesn't come back.

609
00:38:49,310 --> 00:38:50,971
- Suits me.
- Ever.

610
00:38:51,045 --> 00:38:52,979
You know, you're one lucky son of a bitch.

611
00:38:53,047 --> 00:38:56,949
Hey. Hey, um- Can I borrow him
for a minute? Just personal stuff.

612
00:38:57,018 --> 00:38:58,883
Yeah. Just- Just make it-

613
00:38:58,953 --> 00:39:00,944
quick.

614
00:39:01,022 --> 00:39:03,855
I knew you were up to something
the moment you walked into my office!

615
00:39:03,924 --> 00:39:07,382
Then I had to sit there and watch you play
me like one of those yuppies back in London!

616
00:39:07,461 --> 00:39:09,326
McClellan had me
by the short and curliest, Cal.

617
00:39:09,397 --> 00:39:12,161
- My best mate!
- Oh, come on! You think I wanted to do it?

618
00:39:12,233 --> 00:39:13,996
You were in on this from the start, Terry!

619
00:39:14,068 --> 00:39:17,401
They knew who I was before I even sat down
at that poker table.

620
00:39:17,471 --> 00:39:19,962
What was that?
That was just some little test run.

621
00:39:20,041 --> 00:39:21,736
- So what do you call this, eh?
- That?

622
00:39:21,809 --> 00:39:26,212
A couple of broken fingers
for a slice of that pie? Do me a favor.

623
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:28,874
And you can stop treating me
like a bloody moron now.

624
00:39:28,949 --> 00:39:31,213
Yeah, well, maybe I just
came to resent you, Cal.

625
00:39:31,285 --> 00:39:35,221
Hate me, more like. Eh?
Years will do that, Terry.

626
00:39:35,289 --> 00:39:38,850
You saw all the way through it, didn't you?
You saw right through it from the start.

627
00:39:40,428 --> 00:39:44,091
Still helped me though,
didn't you? You know why?

628
00:39:44,165 --> 00:39:49,432
'Cause you always have been
and you always will be my best mate.

629
00:39:49,503 --> 00:39:53,030
Don't count on it, all right?

630
00:39:53,107 --> 00:39:55,166
I'll tell you what.

631
00:39:55,242 --> 00:39:59,178
My debt is now paid in full.

632
00:39:59,246 --> 00:40:02,340
No. Wait a sec. Wait a sec.
You owe me now.

633
00:40:02,416 --> 00:40:06,011
Yeah, I saved your bacon,
and I covered your ass with the F.B.I.

634
00:40:06,087 --> 00:40:07,884
I'm a very lucky man.

635
00:40:07,955 --> 00:40:09,889
Yeah.

636
00:40:12,226 --> 00:40:15,684
Well, all luck is earned, in the end.

637
00:40:17,164 --> 00:40:19,530
Well, go on, then. Off you go.

638
00:40:31,178 --> 00:40:33,442
Don't you dare look back!

639
00:40:50,798 --> 00:40:52,629
Hi.

640
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:55,635
- Have a seat.
- Why?

641
00:40:55,703 --> 00:40:58,900
- This is an intervention.
- What?

642
00:41:01,041 --> 00:41:03,976
All right. So I had a, you know,
few drinks with a mate.

643
00:41:04,044 --> 00:41:08,242
- Yeah, well- More than a few, actually.
- This isn't about drinking.

644
00:41:08,315 --> 00:41:12,615
Well, then if it's about poker,
I won a hundred grand.

645
00:41:12,686 --> 00:41:16,053
- Hundred grand?
- Uh, hundred and five, actually.

646
00:41:16,123 --> 00:41:18,114
It's not about gambling either.

647
00:41:18,192 --> 00:41:20,183
- What is it about then?
- It's about you trusting us.

648
00:41:20,261 --> 00:41:23,128
You were in trouble,
and you never came to us.

649
00:41:23,197 --> 00:41:25,324
- Wait a minute.
- No, you wait.

650
00:41:25,399 --> 00:41:28,664
We're a team, and you risked your life
without letting us help you.

651
00:41:28,736 --> 00:41:33,173
Look, I wouldn't be here at all
if it wasn't for Terry Marsh.

652
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:35,140
Fine. So where does that leave us?

653
00:41:35,209 --> 00:41:39,942
- That leaves you all fired.
- You gotta be kidding.

654
00:41:40,014 --> 00:41:42,448
- I didn't even want to do this intervention thing.
- Just you then.

655
00:41:42,516 --> 00:41:44,848
Just you are fired- for having no spine.

656
00:41:44,919 --> 00:41:48,150
- I don't believe this.
- Good. 'Cause I'm lying'.

657
00:41:48,222 --> 00:41:50,122
Oh, what? You didn't spot that?

658
00:41:50,191 --> 00:41:53,991
Oh, did your emotions get in the way?
You should really work on that.

659
00:41:54,061 --> 00:41:57,792
Well, this has been terrific.

660
00:41:57,865 --> 00:41:59,628
Really fantastic.

661
00:41:59,700 --> 00:42:01,429
Quite the intervention.

662
00:42:01,502 --> 00:42:04,494
We should do this again soon, very soon.

663
00:42:09,710 --> 00:42:11,541
The intervention was my idea.

664
00:42:22,923 --> 00:42:27,053
My mum died when I was young,
and my dad was long gone by then.

665
00:42:27,127 --> 00:42:32,064
Terry and his family, they took me in, even
though there was no room, even less money.

666
00:42:32,132 --> 00:42:36,091
And one day, um, Terry and I got into
a little bit of trouble with the police.

667
00:42:36,170 --> 00:42:40,732
Not your concern.
But... they were on their way...

668
00:42:40,808 --> 00:42:43,174
and there was no way
we could get out of it...

669
00:42:43,244 --> 00:42:46,042
without one of us
acting as a decoy for the other.

670
00:42:46,113 --> 00:42:48,911
- So Terry took the fall for you?
- Yeah, he did.

671
00:42:48,983 --> 00:42:51,144
He said that, uh...

672
00:42:51,218 --> 00:42:53,209
"You're supposed to use
that brain of yours for something...

673
00:42:53,287 --> 00:42:56,552
not be dragged down into the muck
by stupid bastards like me. "

674
00:42:57,958 --> 00:43:00,017
- He was right.
- Yeah, he was.

675
00:43:01,362 --> 00:43:04,388
Yeah. Cost him three years of his life.

676
00:43:05,833 --> 00:43:09,530
So anyone who wants to compete
for my loyalty with Terry Marsh...

677
00:43:10,537 --> 00:43:12,198
not really in a fair fight.

678
00:43:16,644 --> 00:43:18,305
Night, love.
